7. TLS Security (HTTPS)
TLS encrypts network traffic.
Example:
Without TLS:
User → HTTP → Application
Anyone can intercept.
With TLS:
User → HTTPS (encrypted) → Application
________________________________________
OpenShift Routes
Routes expose applications externally.
Example:
oc expose service myapp
This creates:
http://myapp-project.apps.cluster.com
Enable TLS:
oc create route edge myroute --service=myservice
Types of TLS routes:
Type	Meaning
edge	TLS terminated at router
passthrough	TLS passed to pod
re-encrypt	Router decrypts and re-encrypts
________________________________________
8. Exposing Applications Using Other Protocols
OpenShift routes mainly support HTTP/HTTPS.
But some apps use:
•	TCP
•	UDP
•	Databases
•	Messaging systems
For these we use:
LoadBalancer
Example:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: db-service
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  ports:
  - port: 3306
  selector:
    app: mysql
________________________________________
9. Multi-Homed Networking
Multi-homed network means:
A pod can have multiple network interfaces
Example:
Pod connected to:
•	Cluster network
•	External storage network
•	Monitoring network
OpenShift uses Multus CNI.
Check network attachment:
oc get network-attachment-definitions
