10. Operators
Operators automate application management.
Operator = automated administrator for an application.
They manage:
•	Install
•	Update
•	Backup
•	Scaling
•	Monitoring
________________________________________
Example Operators:
Operator	Purpose
Prometheus Operator	Monitoring
Elasticsearch Operator	Logging
MySQL Operator	Database
________________________________________
Install Operator
Using CLI:
oc apply -f operator.yaml
Or through OperatorHub in OpenShift console.
Check operators:
oc get csv
CSV = ClusterServiceVersion
________________________________________
11. Cluster Updates
OpenShift supports automated cluster updates.
Admin can update:
•	Kubernetes version
•	OpenShift version
•	Operators
________________________________________
Check cluster version
oc get clusterversion
Example output:
VERSION   AVAILABLE   PROGRESSING
4.18.2    True        False
Update cluster:
oc adm upgrade
